/// Core signature verification logic (pure cryptographic function)
///
/// This function performs the actual cryptographic signature verification without
/// any dependencies on HeaderProvider or contract state. It only requires the
/// cryptographic inputs (public key, signature, payload data).
///
/// # Arguments
/// * `public_key` - Executor's public key (64 bytes, uncompressed)
/// * `block_number` - Block number (from Job.commitBlock)
/// * `tx_hash` - Transaction hash (from Job.id)
/// * `precompile_address` - Precompile address
/// * `precompile_input` - Precompile input bytes
/// * `output` - Execution output bytes
/// * `previous_block_hash` - Previous block hash (from Job.prevHash)
/// * `previous_block_number` - Previous block number (from Job.prevNumber)

/// - Keys sorted lexicographically (using BTreeMap)
/// - Compact serialization (no spaces)
/// - Hex values without 0x prefix
